short.am,ar,bg,bn,ca,cs,da,de,el,en,en_AU,en_G: Applies a filter to currently playing audio and makes it sound like you have left the room.

long.am,ar,bg,bn,ca,cs,da,de,el,en,en_AU,en_G:
When activated, creates a lowpass filter node in the HTML5 Audio API sound graph and routes the sound from all <video> and <audio> tags through it to create the sensation that the audio is being heard through a wall.

Can be used as a focusing tool by taking the edge off of your music so you can concentrate while still enjoying the song in the background.

NOTE: Currently only works with audio played via <audio> and <video> tags like on YouTube and Twitch; support for more sites to come in future versions.
